gain if you’d like to see from     the first stroke. </span></li> <li class=MsoNormal style='tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Culture</b><span     style='font-weight:normal'>: Clicking on the word shows a picture of the     object in the right section. </span></li> <li class=MsoNormal style='tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Assignments</b><span     style='font-weight:normal'>: Clicking on this menu item will bring up a     new browser window. The new browser contains a form that lets you complete     assignments on-line. In the form, type in your name, e-mail address, and     choose your assignment and section number from the pull-down menus. In the     large box, you will type your assignment in English or Japanese as the     assignment requires. Typically, Morton quizzes are in English and other     assignments are in Japanese. See the textbook appendix for input language     setting if Japanese is not installed on your computer.</span></li> <li class=MsoNormal style='tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Main Menu</b><span     style='font-weight:normal'>: This takes you to the Lesson Index page.</span></li></ul><p class=MsoNormal><b>&nbsp;</b></p><p class=MsoNormal><img src="images/play.gif"> Icon by the text:</p><ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc> <li class=MsoNormal style='tab-stops:list .5in'>It starts bringing up the     sound file. It may take a few seconds depending on the speed of your     computer’s processor and RAM. </li></ul><p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;</p><p class=MsoNormal> <img src="images/playall.gif" width="13" height="13"> Icon   under title on Translation page:</p><ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>  <li class=MsoNormal style='tab-stops:list .5in'>It brings up the sound files     for the whole story. This version takes much less time than if each speaker     icon is clicked. As the recording plays, a lever will move slowly to the right,     indicating how much of the recording has played. Move the lever to the left     to rewind the recording in order to hear previous lines.</li></ul><p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;</p><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman"'><b><br clear=ALLstyle='page-break-before:always'></b></span></body></html>